description._content: Catalog #: 09_01164 Title: H. Murray Gibson Special Collection Photo La Crosse Wisconsin Additional Information: Man identified as 'Merv Stikler' seated in cockpit of Aeronca L-2 aircraft at La Crosse Municipal Airport, Wisconsin. Handwritten inscription ""killed in same awhile later while instructing student"", H. Murray Gibson was a bus driver for the Greyhound bus company. He was also an aviation enthusiast who took flying lessons throughout the 1930s. Corporation Name: Aeronca Aircraft Tags: H.
